OL,3,CHow Spain's floods were driven by the
OL,4,CMediterranean's rising temperatures
OL,6,FITV News Science Correspondent Martin
OL,7,FStew explains why extreme weather is
OL,8,Fbecoming more frequent
OL,10,FThe heavy rainfall which has
OL,11,Fdevastated southern Spain was "about
OL,12,F12% heavier and twice as likely" as a
OL,13,Fresult of climate change.
OL,15,FThat's according to World Weather
OL,16,FAttribution which has compared climate
OL,17,Fconditions now to those of the
OL,18,Findustrial revolution. The question is
OL,19,Fwhy?
